section_purpose: To summarize the main contributions of the paper, specifically the introduction of the G4SATBench benchmark and the key insights derived from its evaluation.
key_points: The paper presents G4SATBench, a comprehensive benchmark for evaluating Graph Neural Network (GNN) models in SAT solving.
The benchmark provides curated synthetic SAT datasets from various domains and difficulty levels.
It benchmarks a wide range of GNN-based SAT solvers under diverse settings.
The empirical analysis yields valuable insights into the performance, capabilities, and limitations of GNN-based SAT solvers.
The authors hope G4SATBench will serve as a foundation and inspire future research in GNN-based SAT solving.
dependencies: The content of the entire paper, particularly Sections 4 (G4SATBench), 5 (Benchmarking Evaluation), and 6 (Advancing Evaluation)
